tp://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102494207096731><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>RE: Recommendations ?</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id= >lunaticfringesk</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>124 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jun 24th 2:17 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Actually, I think that we are close to being on the same page, but perhaps I wasnt clear in my earlier message.<br><br>AC is king most of the time.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am 100% all about improving SK tanking &amp; high AC is probably the #1 attribute to have to improve that.  I was referring to CORE STATS only (STR/STA/INT, etc)<br><br>That said, I WOULD sacrifice STA to obtain a higher AC (as long as STA doesnt drop below 100 that is), as I do believe that the reduction in damage from a higher AC is probably greater than the additional HP that is given from a higher STA.  <br><br>His message, however, seemed to indicate that the difference between the AC was immaterial &amp; that he was choosing between INT gear vs STR/STA gear.  In that case, the decision is simple to me&amp;#8212;choose the STR/STA gear.  An exception, however, is fear-kiting, where INT might reign over STR/STA gear.<br><br>One case, however, where AC is NOT king is reverse-kiting.  In that case, AC means very little, assuming all goes well, as you arent hit that much at all.  As a matter of fact, a CLR is probably one of your worst partners (unless kiting undead) because their greatest attribute (healing) is rendered almost useless.<br><br>When referring to CORE STATISTICS, unless my character was a complete DOLT (i.e. INT of 70 or something), I would choose STA gear over INT gear every day of the week &amp; twice on Sunday.  Damage wise, an SKs spells are fairly weak &amp; it isn&amp;#8217;t until 59 (cascading darkness) that we finally get a decent DoT (you wanna talk getting agro, THAT SPELL DOES IT).  Yes, I really like Boil Blood, but that is no difference maker at all unfortunately.<br><br>In case that you doubt my opinion, let me assure you that I am not alone in my thinking&amp;#8230;..   =P<br><br>From castersrealm.com &amp; how to assign your starting points at inception of an SK character:<br><br>Stamina affects how many hit points you have, and how long you can hold your breath.  It is a very important statistic for Shadow Knights as they are often secondary tanks.  Furthermore, it is the hardest statistic to raise through items.  We would recommend putting a majority of your starting points into this.<br><br>When I first made my character, I didnt know this, nor consider this.  Now, with the experience I have obtained, I can assure you that I now agree 100%.  STA, when referring to core stats only, is KING, as it helps tanking more than any other core stat.<br><br>Lunatic<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
