	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well my last point is on the Clerics again (oh by the way have I mentioned I play one of them too, hehe).&nbsp;&nbsp;Unfortunately I only have 1 account or I'd have hot-boxed long ago and be a Gravelord and High Priest by now.  And yeh I enjoy discussing this stuff too.<br><br>The reason I perfer Clerics is their ability to fear and stun.  The only times I have ever really gotten into trouble fear-kiting was when I could not get fear to go off and was getting pounded.  So any Class that can fear while I'm getting beat is a great thing for me.  Stun also gives me a chance to get Darkness or fear off while the MOB is right on top of me.  <br><br>The only other real adavntage any other Class brings to fear-kiting is a long duration snare.  If you partner with a Druid or Ranger have them snare and you just keep them feared.  With the longer snare you save bunches of mana and really only have to fear and the MOB will die, and your fear and their snare takes almost no mana.<br><br>Just another thing to look at.<br><br>Neptunis<br>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 56 DE Revenant</td></tr>
